Docker management commands
***********************************
1.command : docker builder prune
   this command is used to mange docker build cache and build system 
   removes unused build cache 

   >when you used to build an image

  command : docker build -t jenkins .
    
    a.docker build : is used build an image
    b.docker builder :is used to manage system
    c.docker builder prune : is used to clean build cache

2.List of networks
  command : docker network ls

  it shows list of networks in the docker 

Network
---------
3.Create a one network 
  command : docker network create web-service

  it can create a network,and check the network create or not
   "docker network ls"

 example :create a two continers in one network
   1.docker run -d --name c1 -p 8080:80 --network web-service nginx    

   2.docker run -d --name c2 -p 8080:80 --network web-service nginx
 
 check the network connection inside the continer by using this command
   "ping <continer-name>"

4.Check the network how many continers can connect this network
   command : docker network inspect network-name

   example :docker network inspect web-service

Volume
--------
5.Check the volumes 
  command : docker volume ls
  
  this command shows list of volumes

6.Create the volumes 
  command : docker volume create volume-name

  example : docker volume create web-date
  
  check the volume is create or not "docker volume ls"

7.Create a continer with volumes
  command& example: docker run -d --name web -p 8080:80 -v web-data:/usr/share/nginx/html nginx

 if you delete the continer the data can be stored in volume,and create the same continer again with the volume the file data can be stored in the continer 

continer
----------
8.List of all running container

 command : docker container ls

9.List of all continer including stopped container also
 
 command : docker continer ls -a

10.Create a continer

 command&example : docker container run -itd --name jenkins almalinux /bin/bash

11.Stop a container

 command : docker continer stop continer-id

 example : docker container stop 7fa
 
12.Start a continer

 command : docker container start continer-id

 example : docker container 7fa

13.Restart a continer

 command : docker container restart continer-id

 example : docker continer restart 7fa

14.Remove a continer

 command : docker container rm continer-id

 example : docker container rm 7fa

15.Enter into inside the continer

 command : docker exec -it continer-id /bin/bash

 example : docker exec -it 7fa /bin/bash

16.Force to remove the continer
 
 command : docker container rm -f container-id

